Resource.description:
A resource is an entity with an independent life cycle from other entities.  The concept is taken from REST but is similar to the Aggregate Business Entity of the TmForum SID and also from <a href="http://martinfowler.com/bliki/DDD_Aggregate.html"><font color="#0563c1"><u>http://martinfowler.com/bliki/DDD_Aggregate.html</u></font></a>and <a href="https://vaughnvernon.co/?p=879"><font color="#0563c1"><u>https://vaughnvernon.co/?p=879</u></font></a> ROADSIDE_ASSISTANCE_REQUEST[This is a request for roadside assist for any direct line of business brand.], CLAIM, QUOTE_DOCUMENT, CUSTOMER, PERSON_CONTACT, ANY[Any resource], POLICY_PAYMENT, CONTENT[Content which is shared between a customer and the IAG business.
This is equivalent to CommunicationContent in the IAGIAA model.], ACCOUNT, PAYMENT[A transfer of money between two party's or between two money repositories of the same party. A payment could be made either by the modelled organisation or by a third party. For example a premium contribution of EUR 100 for the payment of the term life packaged with a mortgage. Another example would be an individual benefit payment of EUR 1000 made by Soar Insurance Corp in settlement of an invalidity claim of EUR 1000 per month. ], PROVIDER_AGREEMENT_REQUEST[A request for a change on an existing provider agreemen or a request for issuing a new one, or a request for executing a transaction or service according to the terms and conditions of a provider agreement. A request may be initiated by the provider or by the modelled organisation.], QUOTE, POLICY_PAYMENT_ALLOCATION_FAILURE, SYNTHETIC_TRANSACTION[A transaction generated synthetically only to be used for application service monitoring
],

